description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced, motivated and proactive registered nurse to join the Cardiff and Vale UHB Learning, Education and Development (LED) team as LED Manager for Healthcare Support Worker development. Applications are welcomed from nurses with significant experience of educating healthcare professionals in both classroom and clinical settings and a passion for the development of the unregistered clinical workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the LED senior team the post holder will need to have demonstrable leadership skills, a high level of emotional intelligence and experience of managing teams. A sound understanding of the HCSW development agenda is also essential along with excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Franklin, Senior Nurse for Nurse Education&lt;br /&gt;lisa.franklin@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;02921 845294&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carrie Bodman: Nurse Education Project Coordinator &lt;br /&gt;Carrie.bodman@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;02921 847835&lt;/p&gt;
